1.0 General Information\

\b0 This toolbox contains rigid body transformations presented in 
\i Chapter 3
\i0 , as well as some basic orbit functions from chapter 9.  Toolboxes are provided for the Matlab and Mathematica software packages, as well as C-code libraries in the form of *.c and *.h files.  
\i Appendix E
\i0  of the book lists and explains all the routines provided as they appear in the Matlab toolbox.  Equivalent commands are also provided to Mathematica and C-code users.  Each command has an online help text associated with it that explains its use.  The orbital motion sub-routines are only available to Mathematica and C-code users at this time.\
\

\b 2.0 Installation\

\b0 Both the Matlab and Mathematica toolboxes are plain ASCII text files that must be placed in the proper Matlab or Mathematica sub-folder/sub-directory.  Since the Unix (Mac OS X) and Windows operating system use different ASCII file line endings, two different versions of these ASCII files have been provided which are encoded specifically for each operating system.  If required, these plain text files can be easily converted to other ASCII file formats as needed.  \

