\i 2.3 C-Code
\i0 \
The rigid body kinematics and orbital motion routines are also provided as C-code subroutines in the form of *.c and *.h files.  To use these function, add both the *.c and *.h files to your C-code project or directory, and then using the \
\
	#include "RigidBodyKineamtics.h"\
\
line at the top of your C-code file that will use these subroutines.  Similary, the orbital motion is included using\
\
	#include "orbitalMotion.h"\
\
The files vector3D.c/h are support files for these rigid body kinematics and orbital motion algorithms and allows 3D and 4D vector math to be performed in C.\
